V4L2 with MMAP - Based on ChatGPT prompt for "what is the simplest mmap use of V4L2 for raw data only"

Code outline:
1)  open
2)  set raw format
3)  request buffers
4)  map buffers
5)  queue all buffers
6)  start streaming
7)  dequeue one completed frame
8)  process it
9)  requeue it
10) repeat


6 Essential V4L2 operations:
---------------------------
VIDIOC_REQBUFS
VIDIOC_QUERYBUF
VIDIOC_QBUF
VIDIOC_STREAMON
VIDIOC_DQBUF
VIDIOC_STREAMOFF


Critical Rule:
After DQBUF:
    application owns the buffer

After QBUF:
    driver owns the buffer

https://docs.kernel.org/5.10/userspace-api/media/v4l/vidioc-qbuf.html

Once you call VIDIOC_QBUF, your program must not continue reading or modifying that mapped buffer until it is dequeued again. Queued buffers remain under driver control until dequeued, streaming is stopped, buffers are released, or the device is closed.

For the absolute minimum implementation, two buffers and blocking VIDIOC_DQBUF are sufficient. Using at least two buffers is the safe practical minimum because the device can fill one buffer while the application processes the other.

